criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Single ischemic or haemorrhagic stroke;

          -  Score lower than 100 out of a total of 126 at the Functional Independence Measure
             (FIM) scale

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Untreated epilepsy;

          -  Major depressive disorder;

          -  Fractures;

          -  Traumatic Brain Injurj;

          -  Severe Ideomotor Apraxia;

          -  Severe Neglect;

          -  Severe impairment of verbal comprehension.
